Step 1. Add in your yogurt in a muslin cloth, wrap and tie it around so nothing spills.
Step 2. Once it is secured, put it on a surface where it can hang underneath the sink,
Step 3. Keep the keep the yogurt hung for atleast an hour, or until all of the water has been drained
Step 4. Now you should have a thick hung curd.
Step 5. Now, put your hung curd in a bowl and mix in your desired amount of salt and lemon juice.
Step 6. Your sour cream is ready. Enjoy!